  "prompt": "What are some of the main causes of corruption in third world countries?",
  "response": "Some key factors contributing to corruption in developing countries include:\n\n1. Weak institutional frameworks\n- Ineffective legal systems\n- Poor governance structures\n- Lack of transparency\n\n2. Economic factors\n- Low government salaries\n- High poverty rates\n- Limited economic opportunities\n\n3. Political issues\n- Lack of democratic accountability\n- Concentration of power\n- Weak checks and balances\n\n4. Cultural and social factors\n- Patronage networks\n- Nepotism\n- Acceptance of bribery as a social norm\n\n5. Historical legacies\n- Colonial administrative systems\n- Post-colonial power structures\n- Ongoing foreign economic interventions\n\n6. Limited press freedom\n- Restricted media oversight\n- Difficulties investigating corruption\n- Suppression of whistleblowers\n\n7. Lack of education\n- Limited understanding of democratic principles\n- Low civic engagement\n- Reduced awareness of rights\n\nThese factors often interact and reinforce each other, creating complex challenges for addressing systemic corruption.",
